1 How to Exclude packages:
Double click the shift twice quickly and type excludes and hit enter:
From the pop up window an click + button and select the packages that yuo want to execute.
How Java code is compiled / execute on a computer.
We write the code in file with extension .java
once we hit the run button a software program called compiler checks this code,
 for error and convert it to byte code. usualy stored in a folder called bin/out.
 JVM another software further converts this code to binary code and this binary,
 code is what is excludes on your computer.
 ---------------------------------------------
Why we should packages and class from compiling:
In intellej if we a syntax error in any of the file in a project we can't run the project another
file unless and until we fix that error. Sometimes time we want to execute code in some files without
fixing those issue this is where we should exc.
