Methods in Java:
Method is a block of code. or some java statements (any code with;)grouped together.
Why we should learn about the methods.
Methods help us reduce the amount of code that we have to write.
F.exp if piece of code is being repeated again,
we can create a method for it and simple call that method whenever we need that logic again.
Syntax of creating methods:
 we can create methods only inside a class
 [Datatype][mathod name][(datatype and variable name ---parameters)][method body].
 [Datatype] can we void, boolean, String int etc
 [method name ] they are like variable names .
 [Datatype variable names] used to pass data while calling method.
How do we dicide that we should use void or a method with a return keyword1.
 If we are building a method that will be used by other or in other parts of your code which require
 some data from your meyhod like condition we should not create methods with void type.

