Types of varialbles with respect to ther scape:
There are 3 types of varialbles with respect to there scope:
1. Local variables
2.Instance variables
3. static variables

---Local varialbles
A var-ble that created inside a method switch case any bloc of code called local variable;
WHEN WHEN WE SHOULD use local variables:
**Local variables occupy the computer memory for the amount of time,we should be used local variables,
but, there are limited with in scope we can't use local variables out side of the block in which the are declared.

F.ex for(int i=0; i<5; i++){
System.out.print(i);
}
---Instance variables.
which are declared outside of a block of code but, inside a class are called instance variables.
Int num=1; instance varibles
F.ex for(int i=0; i<5; i++){
System.out.print(i);
}
When we should use  instance variable.
when we are planing to create multiply objects of a class or we want to share something multiply methods,
we should go with instance variables, they occupy the memory for longer as compare to local variables.


---- Static variables.
if an instance has a keyword static with it it called a static variables.
static String name="Rimma";

When we should use static variables?
When we need to share something across the objects. We use static variables.
but, it occupies the memory longest amount of time.





